snippet: Terms coined to help quantify what led to a match’s outcome are more of a hit with the fans and the news media than with the competitors.
abstract: Statistical terms in tennis, like unforced error, are more of a hit with fans and news media than with players and coaches.
lead_paragraph: Terms coined to help quantify what led to a match’s outcome are more of a hit with the fans and the news media than with the competitors.

headline.seo: Tennis Statistics Like Unforced Errors Get No Love From Players
headline.main: Unforced Error Is Unloved Statistic Among Tennis Players
headline.print_headline: Unforced Error Is Unloved Statistic Among Players
